@startuml awslabs_benchmark-ai

actor User
participant "bai-bff" as BFF
participant "executor" as Executor
participant "watcher" as Watcher
participant "sm-executor" as SMExecutor
participant "fetcher-dispatcher" as FetcherDispatcher
participant "fetcher" as Fetcher
participant "metrics-pusher" as MetricsPusher
participant "metrics-extractor" as MetricsExtractor
participant "cloudwatch-exporter" as CloudWatchExporter
queue Kafka
database Kubernetes
database SageMaker
database "AWS CloudWatch" as CloudWatch

User -> BFF: Submit benchmark job
activate BFF

BFF -> Kafka: Publish job submission event
Kafka -> Executor: Consume job submission event
activate Executor
Executor -> Kubernetes: Create job resources
Executor -> Kafka: Publish job created event
deactivate Executor

Kafka -> FetcherDispatcher: Consume job created event
activate FetcherDispatcher
FetcherDispatcher -> Fetcher: Dispatch data fetching job
activate Fetcher
Fetcher -> Fetcher: Download datasets/models
Fetcher -> Kafka: Publish data fetched event
deactivate Fetcher
deactivate FetcherDispatcher

Kafka -> Watcher: Consume data fetched event
activate Watcher
loop Job duration
    Watcher -> Kubernetes: Monitor job status
    Watcher -> SageMaker: Monitor job status
    Watcher -> Kafka: Publish status updates
end
deactivate Watcher

Kafka -> SMExecutor: Consume job events (if SageMaker)
activate SMExecutor
SMExecutor -> SageMaker: Manage SageMaker job lifecycle
SMExecutor -> Kafka: Publish SageMaker job updates
deactivate SMExecutor

loop Job execution
    MetricsPusher -> Kafka: Push job metrics
    MetricsExtractor -> Kafka: Extract and push log metrics
end

Kafka -> CloudWatchExporter: Consume metrics
activate CloudWatchExporter
CloudWatchExporter -> CloudWatch: Export metrics
deactivate CloudWatchExporter

Kafka -> BFF: Consume job status and metric events
BFF -> User: Provide job status and results

deactivate BFF

@enduml